def_en: If an engine is ticking over, it is running at a low speed or rate, for example when it is switched on but you are not actually using it.

def_cn: (人、系统、业务)慢吞吞地工作，进展缓慢
def_en: If a person, system, or business is ticking over, they are working steadily, but not producing very much or making much progress.
